commit.message:
Fix support for the @? jsonb-jsonpath operator

This operator wasn't supported (pg_format would render `@?` as `@ ?`, and although present in the test suite, the SQL in t/pg-test-files/expected/jsonb_jsonpath.sql was invalid:

```
psql (15.2, server 12.14)
Type "help" for help.

radical_db=> SELECT jsonb '1' @ ? '$ ? ((@ == "1") is unknown)';
ERROR:  operator does not exist: ? unknown
LINE 1: SELECT jsonb '1' @ ? '$ ? ((@ == "1") is unknown)';
                           ^
HINT:  No operator matches the given name and argument type. You might need to add an explicit type cast.
radical_db=> SELECT jsonb '1' @? '$ ? ((@ == "1") is unknown)';
 ?column?
----------
 t
(1 row)

radical_db=>
```
Follow the XDG Base Directory Specification by searching configuration file into XDG_CONFIG_HOME/pg_format/config.conf. Thanks to afk-mario for the feature request.
Fix an uninitialized variable error. Thanks to Profpatsch for the report.
Add prerequisite information about the Perl autodie module with RH like distribution. Thanks to Saunders Brandon for the report.
Update ChangeLog and version to 5.5
Prevent newline in function supporting the FROM keyword like substring().
Add multiline formating on TRUNCATE with a table list. Thanks to GabenGar for the feature request.
Remove debug garbage.
Fix not repected --no-space-function behavior with SELECT of function. Thanks to fenuks for the report.
Update regression test result for fix on double quoted alias name. Thanks to Christoph Berg for the report.
Fix potential exception on uninitialized variable. Thanks to Nate Smith for the report.
Fix year in ChangeLog last entry
Update CHangeLog and version to 5.4
